-- Mercosur Mulls Ecuador, Bolivia Membership, Agencia Brasil Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2012-12-02T14:25:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-02/mercosur-mulls-ecuador-bolivia-membership-agencia-brasil-says.html
South America’s  Mercosur  will discuss
the possibility of  Ecuador  and  Bolivia  becoming full members
when leaders of the trade bloc meet in Brasilia on Dec.7,
Brazil’s government news service  Agencia Brasil  reported.  The objective is to deepen South American integration,
Agencia Brasil quote Brazilian Foreign Minister Antonio Patriota
as saying.  Mercosur’s full members are Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay,
Uruguay and Venezuela. Associate members are Chile, Peru,
Ecuador, Bolivia and Colombia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Raymond Colitt in the Brasilia newsroom at 
 rcolitt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman in the Rio de Janeiro newsroom at 
2535 or  jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  